Random (script event)
=====================

Game class
----------

This event operates on an instance of the [Game\_class.html game class] type {{{gameclass}}}

Description
-----------

Returns a random value X where 0 \<= X \< range.

Usage
-----

float random( float range )

Parameters
----------

-   [range] - a number value that represents the largest possble value to be returned.

Examples
--------

This example generates a random number between `min` and `max`

` `
<font color="#0000ff">`float`</font>` min = `<font color="#0000dd">`10`</font>`;`
<font color="#0000ff">`float`</font>` max = `<font color="#0000dd">`20`</font>`;`
` `
<font color="#0000ff">`float`</font>` rand = min + `<font color="#0000ff">`sys`</font>`.`<font color="#ff0000">`random`</font><font color="#000000">`(`</font>`max - min`<font color="#000000">`)`</font>`;`

Notes
-----

Returns the same set of random numbers every time the game is run. Just change the seed for a different set of numbers.


